Jerkbait season is finally here!! This Livingston 121C has caught over 100 bass and it’s still talking! We made this bait to be a slow sink jerkbait. Now with Active Target live sonar, I want it to sink even faster to fish it deeper, so I’ll add this size 4 bladed hook in the center, as well as the Daiichi 4X heavier wire, bleeding bait treble in the front. You need to try this set up for those fish suspended around bait balls in 8 to 15 feet of water. The Livingston patented shad sound draws them to you even when it’s not moving! It WILL CATCH THEM!! #bassfishing #freshwater #suspended #electronicbaitfishsounds #trustthescience #bigbass #livingstonlures

This was a clutch fish to put me in the finals last week at Redcrest! The Livingston Jerkmaster 121C is not only good for normal fishing, but also drives em crazy around the beds when they’re chasing away predators. That distressed baitfish sound is what they hear when they’re feeding on bait, and the longer you can keep a Livingston in their zone, the better your chancing are at catching! #bassfishing #jerkbait #fishcanhear #livingstonlures #electronicbaitfishsounds #catchmorefish #redcrestchampionship

This was a miracle catch on Day1 at Douglas! I hooked this 5lb-14oz bass in the back with a small crankbait. It was pulling so hard for so long, I thought it had to be a drum. That’s why you’ve gotta have the best treble hooks on your bait, and a soft tip rod like my signature Tatula Elite cranking rod, and always take your time and assume it’s a bass until you see it! I also learned that Big Bass eat drum! This baby drum was 9” long and looked like a glide bait. Does anybody even make a glide bait to look like a drum🤷‍♂️ I’m just thankful I landed her, and got my Heavy Hitters fish on a stingy lake Douglas! #lucky #bigbass #thankful #blessed #basseatdrum #heavyhitters #mlfheartbeat #tatula #livingstonlures #myyolotek

Day 1 on Gville was a grind! From 20ft deep crankin to even catching a bed fish, it was junk fishing 101!😂 Tomorrow is moving day and we need 17lbs to get it done and move on to the knockout round on Saturday. So keep the prayers coming for a BIG bag tomorrow! Gville has plenty of those BIGS waiting on me! #bigbass #majorleaguefishing #letsgo #rally #livingstonlures #yamamoto

This is how my morning started, and I thought I was about to catch 20lbs quickly! You could see 12-15 big ones on my @lowrancefishing active target2, but I never got another one to bite! The offshore bite is so fickle at Gville right now! I fished 7 schools that I never got a bite out of, and time flies on the scoretracker! So the home lake got me this time, I should’ve stayed shallow to make the cut, then gambled on the schools in the knockout round, but hindsight is 20/20😂 #lessonlearned #shouldacouldawoulda #disappointed #frustrated #thatsfishing #stillblessed #godisgood

ALWAYS take the extra minute to look between and behind docks in tight places!! I’ve caught so many big fish in shallow protected areas like this! This fish was cruising through a bream bed and I got the wacky Senko in front of her quietly before she saw me. Being quick and quiet with your cast is the key to success around bream beds! My favorite color is green pumpkin/purple/green flake, wacky style tied straight to 20lb green J-braid grand on a 1/0 ProX wacky hook. This setup works great for all cruising Bass!

The Neko rigged Slinko is a fairly new bait that’s really impressed me this season!! I’ve started mixing this in with my wacky Senko, and it’s a different look for heavily pressured fish! I rig it with a wacky ring band just above the egg sack area. I’m using a 1/0 ProX wacky/Neko hook with a 12lb Jfluoro leader tied to 15lb Jbraid grand. Give this bait a try and you’re gonna love it! #bassfishing #largemouthbass #smallmouthbass #wacky #neko #slinko #funfishing

Day 2 and changing it up!

St. Clair didn’t go like I expected! I still don’t know how I had such a bad first day! I needed to rally on day2, so I went up to the mouth of Lake Huron in the river where the potential is there to catch 25+lbs. I had a great day catching fish, and weighed over 17lbs, but this fish was my heavy hitters fish, and could’ve put me over 20lbs. It looked to be a 5pounder, but the swimbait popped out while she was twisting and turning in that fast current! It was the only one that got off all week, but it was the biggest one! And that summed up my tournament, so close, but so far away! Now I need to shake this little slump I’ve had the past two months. The tournament fishing game is an emotional roller coaster and very much played in your head, and after 30 yrs of doing it, it never gets any easier!🤷‍♂️ #smallmouthbassfishing #humbling #badevent #regroup #shakeitoff #betterdaysarecoming #needabreak #godisgood #wewillovercome #livingstonlures

Day 1 Saginaw Bay!

Had some good topwater action in Lacrosse, Wisconsin at the Invitational. Always try a topwater Walking Boss first anywhere you go up north in the summer. Largemouth and smallmouth both love to feed on top! Always make long cast with 50lb Jbraid grand. I use my Daiwa Tatula elite 7’4” Big topwater rod, and 8.1 retrieve Tatula elite reel. This set up will give you the best hookup ratio.  I love Topwater! #bassfishing #largemouthbass #smallmouthbass #backtoback #mixedbag #goodmorning #goodtimes #livingstonlures #walkingboss

After millions of casts, my elbow needed a little maintenance.  Yesterday I went to Dr. Ketchum(best name ever) with @andrews_sports_medicine 
and he did a PRP procedure on my arm. If you aren’t familiar, this is where they take blood out of the opposite arm, spin it to separate the plasma from the blood, and then inject the plasma into the area that needs healing! He numbed the area before injecting the plasma. It’s a very easy and effective treatment for overuse of the elbow that causes tendinitis. I’ve had this done once on each arm about 5-6 years ago and it works great!! #victoryoverinjury #andrewssportsmedicine #fishinginjury #drketchum #IbethecanKetchum
